{"info": {"author": "Taiki Oyama", "author_email": "oyamat4@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "SREM estimates surface reflectance of satellite imagery without integrating information of aerosol particles and\natmospheric gasses. Core algorithm is based on \"A Simplified and Robust Surface Reflectance Estimation Method (SREM) for Use over DiverseLand Surfaces Using Multi-Sensor Data\" [[pdf](https://www.mdpi.com/2072-4292/11/11/1344/pdf)]. \n\n\n### Installation\nThis library supports Python >= 3.6\n```sh\npip install srem\n```\n\n### Usage\n```python\nimport numpy as np\nfrom srem import srem\n\nsurface_reflectance = srem(\n    toa_reflectance, # np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)\n    wavelength, # float in micrometer\n    solar_azimuth_angle_deg, # float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)\n    solar_zenith_angle_deg, # float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)\n    sensor_azimuth_angle_deg, # float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)\n    sensor_zenith_angle_deg # float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)\n)\n\nassert isinstance(surface_reflectance, np.ndarray)\nassert surface_reflectance.shape == toa_reflectance.shape\n```\n\nFor detailed usage, please refer to examples of Landsat-8 and Sentinel-2.\n- [example/landsat8](https://github.com/oyam/srem/tree/master/examples/landsat8)\n- [example/sentinel2](https://github.com/oyam/srem/tree/master/examples/sentinel2)\n\n\n### References\n- Bilal, Muhammad, et al. \"A simplified and robust surface reflectance estimation method (srem) for use over diverse land surfaces using multi-sensor data.\" Remote Sensing 11.11 (2019): 1344.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/oyam/srem", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT License", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "srem", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/srem/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/srem/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/oyam/srem"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/srem/1.0.1/", "requires_dist": ["numpy (>=1.7)", "flake8 ; extra == 'test'", "mypy ; extra == 'test'", "pytest (>=5.3) ; extra == 'test'"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "A Simplified and Robust Surface Reflectance Estimation Method for Satellite Imagery", "version": "1.0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p>SREM estimates surface reflectance of satellite imagery without integrating information of aerosol particles and\natmospheric gasses. Core algorithm is based on \"A Simplified and Robust Surface Reflectance Estimation Method (SREM) for Use over DiverseLand Surfaces Using Multi-Sensor Data\" [<a href=\"https://www.mdpi.com/2072-4292/11/11/1344/pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">pdf</a>].</p>\n<h3>Installation</h3>\n<p>This library supports Python &gt;= 3.6</p>\n<pre>pip install srem\n</pre>\n<h3>Usage</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">numpy</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"nn\">np</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">srem</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">srem</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">surface_reflectance</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">srem</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">toa_reflectance</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\"># np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">wavelength</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\"># float in micrometer</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">solar_azimuth_angle_deg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\"># float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">solar_zenith_angle_deg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\"># float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">sensor_azimuth_angle_deg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"c1\"># float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">sensor_zenith_angle_deg</span> <span class=\"c1\"># float or np.ndarray with shape of (height, width)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"nb\">isinstance</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">surface_reflectance</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">np</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ndarray</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">surface_reflectance</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shape</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"n\">toa_reflectance</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shape</span>\n</pre>\n<p>For detailed usage, please refer to examples of Landsat-8 and Sentinel-2.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/oyam/srem/tree/master/examples/landsat8\" rel=\"nofollow\">example/landsat8</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/oyam/srem/tree/master/examples/sentinel2\" rel=\"nofollow\">example/sentinel2</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Bilal, Muhammad, et al. \"A simplified and robust surface reflectance estimation method (srem) for use over diverse land surfaces using multi-sensor data.\" Remote Sensing 11.11 (2019): 1344.</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6850085, "releases": {"0.1.11": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9bd344b641d88fc7bb6000c047c37d01", "sha256": "db0275ee63936016826d87ff4834c95bc8a8fb7c92b6cfa2bcd01a012c95c867"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "srem-0.1.11-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9bd344b641d88fc7bb6000c047c37d01", "packagetype": "bdis